	h1={`The Bible for Those Grieving a Loss`}
	heroEyebrow={`A Father For`}
	heroSubhead={`If you have lost someone you love — to suicide, to violence, to a death that came without warning — there are no words that make it right, and we will not pretend otherwise. But there is a Father who does not look away from your grief. He is close to the brokenhearted, He keeps every tear, and He has not turned away from you.`}
	heroBase={`https://cdn.sanity.io/images/rusi1hyi/production/88b47dc15aa46bc5d5348640ad634e5a278b804c-1100x733.jpg`}
	heroAlt={`The first light of dawn breaking behind a tree after the dark of night`}
	heroObjectPosition={`center center`}
	directAnswerHtml={`<strong style="color: var(--color-ink);">If you are grieving the loss of someone you love, the Father's Heart Bible™ is for you.</strong> Maybe the loss came through suicide, through murder, through a sudden death no one saw coming — and the grief is unlike anything words can hold. Whether you searched "Bible verses for grief," "comfort after the loss of a loved one," "comfort in mourning," or "verses for suicide loss survivors," please know this first: the answer to a loss this heavy is not a tidy explanation. It is a Father who weeps with you. The <a href="https://fathersheartbible.com/read" style="color: var(--color-brand);" class="hover:underline">Father's Heart Bible™</a> is a fresh English translation you can read and <em>listen to</em> free — and it reveals God as a <em>Father</em> who is close to the brokenhearted, who collects every tear, and who has not let go of you in the dark.`}
	keyTakeaway={`There is no grief too heavy for the Father to hold with you. He is close to the brokenhearted, He keeps every tear you have cried, and He has not turned away.`}
	painsHeading={`The weight of a loss like this`}
	painsIntroHtml={`Grief after a sudden, violent, or traumatic loss is its own kind of heavy — tangled with shock, with "what if," with anger and questions that have no answers. If you are carrying this, you are not alone in it, and the weight you feel is real.`}
	painStats={[
		{ value: `49,000+`, label: `people died by suicide in the United States in a single recent year, each one leaving family and friends behind (CDC, 2023)` },
		{ value: `135`, label: `people, on average, are affected by each death by suicide — a wide circle of survivors left to grieve (AFSP)` },
		{ value: `19,000+`, label: `people died by homicide in the United States in a recent year, leaving co-victims behind to mourn a loved one (CDC, 2023)` },
		{ value: `~10%`, label: `of bereaved people experience prolonged, complicated grief — and the rate is higher after a sudden or violent death (research review)` },
		{ value: `1 in 5`, label: `Americans report knowing someone who has died by suicide in the past year, a grief that touches whole communities (AFSP)` },
		{ value: `Higher`, label: `rates of depression, anxiety, and post-traumatic stress are seen among those bereaved by suicide and violent loss (National Alliance for Children's Grief)` },
	]}
	painsBodyHtml={`<p>Behind every number is a face, a name, a person you loved and a hole where they used to be. Maybe the grief comes in waves that knock you down without warning. Maybe it is tangled with guilt — the endless "what if" and "if only" that replays in the quiet. Maybe there is anger you do not know where to put, or a faith that suddenly has more questions than answers. Maybe the hardest part is how alone it feels, because so many people simply do not know what to say.</p><p>None of this means your faith is failing or that you are grieving wrong. There is no wrong way to carry a loss like this. It means you loved someone deeply, and love that deep does not let go easily. There is a Father who sees every bit of it — the tears, the silence, the questions you cannot voice — and He does not flinch, and He does not leave.</p>`}
	painsSources={[
		{ label: `CDC — Facts About Suicide`, url: `https://www.cdc.gov/suicide/facts/index.html` },
		{ label: `American Foundation for Suicide Prevention — Suicide Statistics`, url: `https://afsp.org/suicide-statistics/` },
		{ label: `National Alliance for Children's Grief`, url: `https://nacg.org/` },
	]}
	aFatherHeading={`A Father for those grieving a loss`}
	aFatherBodyHtml={`<p>Here is what we will not do: we will not hand you easy answers, or tell you this was part of a plan, or ask you to be okay before you are. A loss like yours deserves more honesty than that. What we can tell you is true, and it has held people in the darkest valleys there are: there is a <strong style="color: var(--color-ink);">Father</strong> who does not stand at a distance from your grief. He draws near to the brokenhearted. He saves the crushed in spirit.</p><p>This Father does not explain your pain away. He enters it. When Jesus stood at the grave of His friend, He did not rush to fix it — He wept. That is the heart of God toward loss: not cold, not detached, but tears on His own face. He weeps with you. And He is strong enough to hold what you cannot carry on your own.</p><p>So in the nights when the grief feels endless, when the questions have no answers and the silence is loud, you are not abandoned. Your Father is close. He keeps every tear in His care. And He has promised that a day is coming when He Himself will wipe them away — not because your loss did not matter, but because it mattered to Him more than you know.</p>`}
