	verses={[
		{ ref: `Psalm 34:18`, slug: `psalms`, ch: 34, text: `Your Father is close to the brokenhearted, and He saves those whose spirits are crushed.`, note: `When your heart is broken in pieces, He does not stand far off — He comes near, on purpose, to be with you.` },
		{ ref: `Psalm 147:3`, slug: `psalms`, ch: 147, text: `He heals the brokenhearted and binds up their wounds, tending each one with His own hands.`, note: `Your Father does not rush your healing — He tends the wound gently, the way a parent cares for a hurting child.` },
		{ ref: `Matthew 5:4`, slug: `matthew`, ch: 5, text: `Blessed are those who mourn, for they will be comforted by their Father.`, note: `Your mourning is not a sign you are failing — it is met with His comfort, held by His own promise.` },
		{ ref: `Revelation 21:4`, slug: `revelation`, ch: 21, text: `Your Father will wipe away every tear from their eyes, and death will be no more, nor mourning, nor crying, nor pain — for the old order has passed away.`, note: `He does not promise the tears never came — He promises a day when His own hand will wipe the last one away.` },
		{ ref: `Psalm 56:8`, slug: `psalms`, ch: 56, text: `You have kept count of my wanderings; put my tears in Your bottle. Are they not written in Your book?`, note: `Not one tear you have cried has been wasted or unseen — your Father has kept every single one.` },
		{ ref: `2 Corinthians 1:3-4`, slug: `2-corinthians`, ch: 1, text: `Blessed be the Father of mercies and the God of all comfort, who comforts us in all our affliction, so that we may comfort others with the comfort we have received.`, note: `He is named the Father of mercies and the God of all comfort — comfort is not a side note to Him; it is who He is.` },
		{ ref: `Isaiah 41:10`, slug: `isaiah`, ch: 41, text: `Do not be afraid, for I am with you; do not be dismayed, for I am your Father. I will strengthen you and help you; I will hold you up with My righteous right hand.`, note: `When you have no strength left to stand, He promises to hold you up Himself.` },
		{ ref: `John 11:35`, slug: `john`, ch: 11, text: `Jesus wept.`, note: `Standing at the grave of someone He loved, God in the flesh wept. Your tears are never beneath Him — He shares them.` },
		{ ref: `Psalm 23:4`, slug: `psalms`, ch: 23, text: `Even though I walk through the valley of the shadow of death, I will fear no evil, for You are with me; Your rod and Your staff, they comfort me.`, note: `He does not promise to keep you out of the valley — He promises to walk every step of it beside you.` },
	]}
	offersHeading={`What "our Father" offers you`}
	offersIntroHtml={`Grief like this cannot be fixed with words. Here is not a solution, but a Presence — what your Father offers you in the middle of the loss, freely, because He is near.`}
	offersBlocks={[
		{ heading: `Nearness to the brokenhearted`, bodyHtml: `Your Father is <a href="https://fathersheartbible.com/read/psalms/34" style="color: var(--color-brand);" class="hover:underline">close to the brokenhearted</a> — not waiting for you to feel better, but drawing near precisely because your spirit is crushed.` },
		{ heading: `A keeper of every tear`, bodyHtml: `Not one of your tears has gone unnoticed. Your Father <a href="https://fathersheartbible.com/read/psalms/56" style="color: var(--color-brand);" class="hover:underline">keeps each one</a>, counted and held — your grief is seen, and it is sacred to Him.` },
		{ heading: `A God who weeps with you`, bodyHtml: `He is not distant from your pain. At a friend's grave, <a href="https://fathersheartbible.com/read/john/11" style="color: var(--color-brand);" class="hover:underline">Jesus wept</a> — and that same heart weeps with you now, sharing the sorrow rather than explaining it away.` },
		{ heading: `A promise that this is not the end`, bodyHtml: `Your Father promises a day when He will <a href="https://fathersheartbible.com/read/revelation/21" style="color: var(--color-brand);" class="hover:underline">wipe every tear away</a>, and death and mourning will be no more. The grief is real — and so is the hope that it does not have the last word.` },
	]}
	whyHeading={`Why the Father's Heart Bible™ in grief`}
	whyBlocks={[
		{ heading: `You meet a Father who weeps, not a distant deity`, bodyHtml: `Grief can make God feel far away. The Father's Heart Bible™ reveals God as a <em>Father</em> wherever Scripture does — a Father who is close to the brokenhearted, and a God who, in Jesus, <a href="https://fathersheartbible.com/read/john/11" style="color: var(--color-brand);" class="hover:underline">wept at a grave</a>. You do not meet a cold explainer of your pain. You meet One who shares it.` },
		{ heading: `Free, with audio, for the sleepless nights`, bodyHtml: `Grief does not keep daytime hours. <a href="https://fathersheartbible.com/read" style="color: var(--color-brand);" class="hover:underline">Read it free online</a> with audio on every chapter — so when you cannot sleep, cannot focus, cannot find your own words, you can simply listen and let His voice be near in the dark. No account, no purchase, no app.` },
		{ heading: `It speaks gently to mourning`, bodyHtml: `When you do not know what to pray or where to turn, start with our <a href="/verses/" style="color: var(--color-brand);" class="hover:underline">verses by topic</a> or our <a href="/guides/how-to-pray/" style="color: var(--color-brand);" class="hover:underline">how-to-pray guide</a> — gentle places to begin when grief has taken your words away.` },
	]}
	voicesHeading={`The Father's heart, in their words`}
	voicesIntroHtml={`There is no grief too heavy for the Father to hold with you. The truth beneath every verse here, that God is before anything else a Father close to the brokenhearted, is the one these voices gave their lives to:`}
	voices={[
		{ quote: `Answered prayer is the interchange of love between the Father and His child.`, name: `Andrew Murray`, role: `who taught a generation to live as the Father's children`, photo: `https://cdn.sanity.io/images/rusi1hyi/production/133bc45cfa954cf1ae99b7afac5954eca764ed70-500x830.jpg` },
		{ quote: `The hardest, gladdest thing in the world is, to cry Father! from a full heart.`, name: `George MacDonald`, role: `who taught that the Fatherhood of God is the heart of the gospel`, photo: `https://cdn.sanity.io/images/rusi1hyi/production/35e71c2610893383d20b60883aa0b1d4d4664cbc-500x726.jpg` },
		{ quote: `There is heaven in the depth of that word — Father.`, name: `Charles Spurgeon`, role: `the “Prince of Preachers”`, photo: `https://cdn.sanity.io/images/rusi1hyi/production/e48a128da123135241be9c95cf35b37498d94ea5-500x617.jpg` },
	]}
	voicesCreditHtml={`Photos via <a href="https://commons.wikimedia.org/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" style="color: var(--color-brand);" class="hover:underline">Wikimedia Commons</a> &mdash; Andrew Murray, George MacDonald, and Charles Spurgeon (all public domain).`}
	wordHeading={`His Word will not return void`}
	wordBodyHtml={`<p>You may not feel comforted the first time you open it, or the tenth. Grief does not work on a schedule, and the Father is not in a hurry with you. His nearness is not a feeling you have to manufacture — it is a faithfulness that holds you even when you feel nothing at all. Every gentle word you take in is your Father staying close, holding what you cannot carry, one breath at a time.</p><p class="mt-4" style="color: var(--color-ink);">"My word… will not return to me empty, but will accomplish that which I purpose." <span style="color: var(--color-muted);">— Isaiah 55:11</span></p>`}
	fatherSaysHeading={`What your Father says over you`}
	fatherSaysHtml={`<p>"I am close to you in this. I know the name you are grieving, the empty place at the table, the questions you cannot speak aloud. I have not turned away from you, and I have not turned away from the one you lost. I see your tears, and I have kept every one of them — not a single one has fallen unnoticed.</p><p>I will not rush you, and I will not ask you to pretend you are alright before you are. I only ask you to let Me stay near. When the weight is more than you can carry, give Me what you cannot hold. I am your Father. I am here in the dark with you, and I am not leaving."</p>`}
	prayerHeading={`A prayer for those grieving a loss`}
	prayerHtml={`<p>Our Father, we come to You carrying a grief almost too heavy for words — the loss of someone deeply loved, gone in a way that has left wounds we cannot reach. We will not pretend to understand it, and we ask You not for tidy answers but for Your nearness. Draw close, Father, to every broken heart reading this prayer.</p><p>You have promised to be near to the brokenhearted and to save the crushed in spirit. Be that for them now. Hold what they cannot carry. Keep every tear they have cried, as You have promised You do. Where there is guilt and "what if," be gentle. Where there is anger, do not be afraid of it. Where faith feels shattered, hold them anyway with Your own hands.</p><p>Comfort them in the long nights and the sudden waves. Send people who will sit with them and not rush them. And let them feel, even faintly, that You have not left — that You weep with them, that You are with them in the valley, and that the day is coming when You Yourself will wipe away every tear.</p><p>In Jesus' name, amen.</p>`}
