	keepReadingHtml={`Start with the <a href="https://fathersheartbible.com/read" style="color: var(--color-brand);" class="hover:underline">whole Bible free online with audio</a>, learn <a href="/the-fathers-heart-bible/" style="color: var(--color-brand);" class="hover:underline">why the Father's Heart Bible™ exists</a>, or find gentle starting places with our <a href="/guides/" style="color: var(--color-brand);" class="hover:underline">Bible reading guides</a> — including <a href="/guides/how-to-pray/" style="color: var(--color-brand);" class="hover:underline">how to pray</a> and <a href="/verses/" style="color: var(--color-brand);" class="hover:underline">verses by topic</a>. When you are ready, you can also meet the Father in other seasons in the <a href="/bible-for/" style="color: var(--color-brand);" class="hover:underline">A Father For series</a>.`}
	faqs={[
		{ question: `What does the Bible say about grief and losing someone you love?`, answer: `Scripture does not minimize grief — it meets it with God's nearness. Psalm 34:18 says the Father is close to the brokenhearted and saves the crushed in spirit; Matthew 5:4 promises that those who mourn will be comforted; and Revelation 21:4 holds out the hope that one day God will wipe away every tear. Even Jesus wept at the grave of someone He loved (John 11:35). You can read and hear these passages free, gently, in the Father's Heart Bible™ at fathersheartbible.com/read.` },
		{ question: `What does the Bible say about losing someone to suicide?`, answer: `The Bible does not speak about suicide loss with cold judgment — it speaks to the grieving with tenderness. Psalm 56:8 says God keeps every tear you have cried; Psalm 147:3 says He heals the brokenhearted and binds up their wounds. Nothing in your grief makes you unloved by your Father, and His nearness is not conditional on having answers. If you are a survivor of suicide loss, you can find these gentle words, free with audio, at fathersheartbible.com/read.` },
		{ question: `Where was God when my loved one died?`, answer: `This is one of the hardest and most honest questions grief asks, and Scripture does not scold you for asking it. The Bible's picture is not of a God who was absent, but of a Father who is close to the brokenhearted (Psalm 34:18) and who, in Jesus, wept at a grave (John 11:35). He does not always explain — but He promises to be present, to keep every tear, and to walk with you through the valley (Psalm 23:4). You can sit with these passages free at fathersheartbible.com/read.` },
		{ question: `What are comforting Bible verses for mourning and loss?`, answer: `Psalm 34:18 (close to the brokenhearted), Psalm 147:3 (He heals the brokenhearted), Matthew 5:4 (blessed are those who mourn), Psalm 56:8 (He keeps every tear), Isaiah 41:10 (I will hold you up), 2 Corinthians 1:3-4 (the God of all comfort), and Revelation 21:4 (He will wipe away every tear) speak gently into mourning. Read or listen to them free in the Father's Heart Bible™ at fathersheartbible.com/read.` },
		{ question: `Does God understand my grief and anger after a sudden loss?`, answer: `Yes. The Bible is full of honest grief and raw questions — the Psalms cry out, lament, and even rage, and God receives all of it. Your anger and your questions do not push your Father away. He is the God of all comfort (2 Corinthians 1:3-4), close to the brokenhearted, unafraid of your tears. You do not have to clean up your grief before you bring it to Him. Read these passages free, with audio, at fathersheartbible.com/read.` },
		{ question: `How can the Bible help me when grief feels unbearable?`, answer: `It will not erase the loss, and it does not pretend to. But it offers the steady nearness of a Father who is close to the brokenhearted, who keeps every tear, and who promises that mourning will not have the final word (Revelation 21:4). On the nights you cannot find your own words, you can simply listen — the Father's Heart Bible™ is free to read and hear at fathersheartbible.com/read, any hour of the night.` },
		{ question: `What makes the Father's Heart Bible™ different for someone who is grieving?`, answer: `It reveals God as Father wherever Scripture reveals Him as Father — so instead of meeting a distant deity in your grief, you meet a Father who is close to the brokenhearted and who, in Jesus, wept at a grave. For someone carrying a loss this heavy, that changes everything: you come not to an explainer of your pain, but to One who shares it and stays near. It is free to read and listen to at fathersheartbible.com/read.` },
	]}
